I wouldn't say overdesigned, but it's a very awkward and unappealing design to me.

It's like, deliberately low model detail in an era where that's just not needed, but it's not exploiting the techniques used in the low model detail era to make the most of what they had.

Overall the creature is flat primer gray. Gray is gray, and artists know that working with gray is about working with value, but that's been deliberately avoided for much of the figure.

Then there is the clothing which is apparently trying to nod to a century old aesthetic which is fine, except it's also mostly monochrome and being only a top betrays the more formal implication of the garment while not giving any color.

Looking at >>67199909 the only contrast we get are the vest and its buttons and the eyes. On the body, the bangles and scruncies and horns vanish into the gray grayness if you desaturate the image.

It's like a cargo cult tried to revive an old style. They adopted some of the broad strokes but didn't know how the pieces function together.
